WEBVTT

00:05:55.838 --> 00:06:00.473
The experience you will have there
is deeper than your doubts

00:06:00.497 --> 00:06:04.123
about whether morality
can be anchored to reason.

00:06:04.462 --> 00:06:06.673
And if you think,
"Well, it only burns my hand

00:06:06.697 --> 00:06:10.123
because my mind and body
are constituted in such a way,

00:06:10.147 --> 00:06:12.051
well, yeah, that's precisely the point.

00:06:12.075 --> 00:06:14.240
I'm saying that every possible mind

00:06:14.264 --> 00:06:18.958
is susceptible to a range of experiences,
given the physics of things.

00:06:18.982 --> 00:06:22.618
We don't know how consciousness
is actually integrated with physics.

00:06:22.642 --> 00:06:25.292
That's a mystery,
but there is some relationship,

00:06:25.316 --> 00:06:27.483
and we live in a universe

00:06:27.507 --> 00:06:32.058
where conscious minds
have a range of conscious states,